if you use flask-script in your project, you can create a command in manage.py to run celery:
```python
@manager.option('-n', '--name', help='Your app name')
def celeryworker(name):
    celery_args = ['celery', 'worker', '-n', name, '-C', '--autoscale=10,1', '--without-gossip']
    with app.app_context():
        return celery_main(celery_args)
```
call this command in terminal:
